 *********************************************************************************
   Plane-parallel Cool-MARCS (=MSG) model for Teff =  400. K, log(g) = 3.0
 *********************************************************************************

The model is computed in 53 layers from log_10(tau_ross)= -5.00 to  2.50
 This model of the general type Star/K2_18
meaning that at a scale where epsilon(H) = log(H)=12, epsilon(elm) included:
 12.00 10.93 8.49 7.78 8.74 6.24 7.57 6.47 7.51 5.12 6.38 4.99 4.00 7.42 2.58
  H     He    C    N    O    Na   Mg   Al   Si   K    Ca   Ti   V    Fe   Zr  
The model used  74 molecules/atoms in the opacity computation. They were:
 SO2  TiH  CO2  OH   CrH  CH   AlCl ZrO  PO   NaCl SiS  NO   LiF  HCN  C3   C2H2 MgH  TiO 
 CaH  SiO  LiCl PH3  H2   C2   KCl  HCl  CP   LiH  NaH  AlF  FeH  BeH  MgF  CaF  CH4  CO  
 CN   H2CO NH3  AlO  VO   SiH  PN   CS   KF   H2O  PS   SN   AlH  NaF  HS   NH   Al   Be  
 Ca   Cl   C    Cr   Fe   F    K    Li   Mg   Na   N    O    P    Si   S    Ti   V    Zr  
 O2   O3  
The OS cross sections (cm2/molecule) were read into  7949 wavenumbers between
 400.0 and 80000.0 cm-1 (= 0.125 to  25. mu). We used only each 10th in the radiative transfer
 of this model, resulting in a (statistical spectral) OS-resolution of 1500.0
 TOTAL FLUX= 1.4368E+06 ERGS/CM**2/S  TEFF=  399. K
 TOTAL FLUX= 1.4367E+06 ERGS/CM**2/S  TEFF=  399. K

Convection was computed based on the parameter choice:
palfa, pbeta, pny, py = 1.5 0.0 8.0 0.076
(but convection was apriori considered irelevant for the uppermost 16 layers)

The convergence criterium was delta(T)= 1.0 K and temp. corr. in the last iteration was 0.00 K


 Technical settings:
dpein,dtin,method-pe,inz.K=12,kort,kpi,mihal,lops,nops: 0.005 0.005 2 4.339eV 5  0 40 0  1
 (listed Pe is from GGchem; Pe for converg. in colm Pturb)

 *********************************************************************************




